UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.On Player Enters Vehicle.D: A player enters the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.On Player Exits Vehicle.De: A player exits the spawned vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.On Vehicle Spawns.Descript: A vehicle is spawned or respawned.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Apply OffRoad Tires.Descri: Apply off-road tires to the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Tire Selection.Description: Choose the type of tires for the spawned vehicle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Boost Fuel Use.Description: Controls how quickly the vehicle will use fuel while boosting.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.FuelUseMultiplier.Descript: Controls how quickly the vehicle will use fuel while driving.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Vehicle Health.Description: Determines how much damage the vehicle can take before destruction.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.BoostRegenMultiplier.Descr: Determines how quickly the boost meter fills.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Boost Enabled.Description: Determines if boost is enabled on vehicle
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Unlimited Boost.Descriptio: Determines if boost should consume fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Vehicle Indestructible.Des: Determines if the Vehicle can be destroyed by damage.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Destroy when Stuck Underwa: Determines if the Vehicle will destroy itself when stuck underwater.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.EnableRespawn.Description: Determines if the Vehicle will respawn after being destroyed.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.FuelConsumption.Descriptio: Determines if the spawned vehicle uses fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Enabled During Phase.Descr: Determines the game phases during which the device will be enabled. If set to CREATE ONLY, will only be enabled while editing your Island.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Max Random Starting Fuel.D: Determines the maximum random fuel percentage the vehicle will spawn with. If Max is less than or equal to Min, the vehicle will spawn with default fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Min Random Starting Fuel.D: Determines the minimum random fuel percentage the vehicle will spawn with. If Max is less than or equal to Min, the vehicle will spawn with default fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.bRadioEnabled.Description: Determines whether spawned vehicle is able to use the radio.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Visible During Game.Descri: Determines whether the device is visible during the game. This does affect its collision properties.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Spawn With Cow Catcher.Des: Determines whether the vehicle has the Cow Catcher when spawned.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Disable.Description: Disable the Vehicle Spawner, stopping it from spawning any more vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Enable.Description: Enable the Vehicle Spawner, allowing it to spawn vehicles.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Allowed Class.Description: If set to All, All Classes (including players with NO CLASS) are affected. Otherwise, the chosen Class will be used to determine the Affects Class effect. ANY CLASS - Players with a Class assigned, regardless of what Class it is. NO CLASS - Players without any assigned class.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Destroy Vehicle.Descriptio: If the vehicle that this spawner created still exists, destroy it.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.bDamageOwnVehicle.Descript: ON will allow collision to damage the player's own vehicle.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.bDamageFriendlyFire.Descri: ON will allow friendly driven vehicles to damage each other on collision.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Allow Damage From Other Ve: ON will allow other vehicles to damage this vehicle by colliding with it. The other vehicles must have Damage Other Vehicles turned on.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.bDamageOtherVehicles.Descr: ON will allow this vehicle to damage other vehicles by colliding with them. The other vehicles must have Allow Damage from Other Vehicles turned on.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Destroy Vehicle When Disab: ON will destroy an already spawned vehicle when this spawner is disabled.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Pop All Tires.Description: Pop all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to pop.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Repair All Tires.Descripti: Repair all of the tires on the vehicle, if the vehicle has tires to repair.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Repair Vehicle.Description: Restore the spawned vehicle to full health.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Remove Tire Modification.D: Revert to road tires on the vehicle if the vehicle can receive them.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Assigns Driver.Description: Seats the player that instigated the message as the spawned vehicle's driver.
UserOptionDefinition.C816F8FC4DD16BF7C38D2398F1337F18: Select what type of Fang to spawn.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Random Starting Fuel.Descr: Spawn the vehicle with a random percentage of fuel.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Respawn Vehicle.Descriptio: Spawns the vehicle (Destroying the existing vehicle if it still exists).
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Activating Team.Descriptio: The Team this device belongs to.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.ExplosionDamageToEnvironme: The amount of damage to deal to environment objects when the vehicle explodes.
The amount of damage to deal to other vehicles when the vehicle explodes.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.ExplosionDamageToPlayers.D: The amount of damage to deal to players when the vehicle explodes.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.LifetimeAfterExplosion.Des: The duration in seconds that the destroyed vehicle will remain in the world, after which it is removed entirely.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Max Explosion Delay.Descri: The maximum time the vehicle can have zero health, after which it will explode.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Starting Fuel.Description: The percentage of fuel in the vehicle's fuel tank at spawn.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Water Destruction Timer.De: When the vehicle becomes too deep in water to drive, destroy it after this delay.
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Respawn Time.Description: When the vehicle is destroyed, respawn it after this delay. (The first vehicle spawned does not use this delay.)
UserOptionDefinition.Device_Fang_C.Respawn Vehicle When Enabl: YES will spawn a vehicle when the device is enabled. ONLY IF NEEDED will not reset an existing vehicle.
